message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey about AI in education. I need to provide responses to 10 statements (TT4G35A through TT4G35J) using one of the five response options: "Strongly disagree", "Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly agree", or "I don't know".

I'm roleplaying as a primary or secondary school teacher from Australia. I should provide thoughtful responses based on realistic perspectives a teacher might have about AI in education. Let me go through each statement:

[TT4G35A]: AI helps teachers write or improve lesson plans.
- This is generally true. AI tools can assist with lesson planning. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35B]: AI enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities.
- This is a reasonable application of AI, though it depends on the implementation. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35C]: AI assists teachers in supporting students individually.
- This can be true with personalized learning systems. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35D]: AI supports students with specific needs (e.g., multilingual learners, students with special education needs).
- AI can provide translations, text-to-speech, etc. This is a strong application area. I would say "Agree" or "Strongly agree". Let me say "Agree"

[TT4G35E]: AI helps teachers automate administrative tasks.
- This is definitely true - grading assistance, attendance, scheduling suggestions, etc. I would say "Strongly agree"

[TT4G35F]: AI enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own.
- This is a concern with AI - students could use it for plagiarism/academic dishonesty. This is true as a risk. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35G]: AI makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct.
- This is a valid concern - AI can make mistakes or provide inaccurate information. 

[TT4G35H]: AI amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions.
- This is a known issue with AI - it can perpetuate biases. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35I]: AI jeopardises the privacy and security of student data.
- This is a legitimate concern with any digital system. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35J]: AI suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students.
- This is possible - AI might not always understand good pedagogical practice. I would say "Agree"

Now I need to structure this as a function.

I'll use the json_tool_call function to format these responses properly.
